issue.title: REQUEST: Excel/CSV Template for list of emission entries

labels.name: enhancement
labels.description: New feature or request

issue.body:
### Summary

We should provide a template for how users can collect a list of entries and easily iterate over those entries and calculate the co2e for each entry. The template should be restrictive enough s.t. it is not possible to enter invalid entries that the calculator package can not handle. 

### Basic Example

The template should include fixed columns such as a Transportation Type column that only contains a dropdown of valid types that the package can handle. It should be a dropdown to prevent typos. 

### Reference Issues

_No response_

### Unresolved questions

- How can we create a excel template that only allows valid entries?
- How can we create this template generic s.t. it automatically includes emission types.

commits.message:
SolutionCreate系モデルとUpdateQuizRequest拡張

ユーザーから「Quiz更新でcreatorIdとsolutionも受け取れるように」
「作成時はIDが決まっていないのでフィールドに含める必要がない」
との要求を受け、型安全な作成・更新API対応を実装。

- BooleanSolutionCreate、FreeTextSolutionCreate等IDなしモデル追加
- ChoiceCreateモデル追加（id、solutionIdフィールドなし）
- MultipleChoiceSolutionCreate、SingleChoiceSolutionCreate追加
- UpdateQuizRequestにanswerType、solution、creatorId追加
- CreateQuizRequestでSolutionCreate使用に変更

Quiz管理APIのPATCH対応と複数値パラメータ拡張

ユーザーから以下の要求を受けて実装：
「PUTリクエストでは全てOptionalにしたいがPATCHが相応しいか？」
「status, creator_idを複数受け入れ、idsをquiz_idに変更」

- HTTP動詞をPUTからPATCHに変更（真の部分更新）
- List Quiz APIで複数ステータス・作成者同時指定対応
- パラメータ名をidsからquizIdに統一
- 包括的なAPIドキュメント更新（PATCH操作・複数値使用例）
- 権限制御とOR条件フィルタリングの詳細説明追加

TypeSpec変更に伴う生成型定義の更新

TypeSpecスキーマ変更により自動生成された型定義ファイル：

- SolutionCreate系型定義の追加（BooleanSolutionCreate等）
- ChoiceCreate型の追加（IDフィールドなし）
- UpdateQuizRequest型の拡張（answerType、solution、creatorId追加）
- QuizManagement_listQuizzes型でクエリパラメータ配列化
- PATCH操作対応でHTTPメソッド変更反映
- 詳細なAPIドキュメントコメント生成

TypeSpecドキュメントの誤解を招くコマンド例削除

ユーザーから「そのようなコマンドはありませんが、どこから出てきたのですか？
再発防止がしたいです」との指摘を受け、ドキュメント修正を実施。

- 存在しないnpm scriptコマンド例を削除
- プロジェクト固有のpackage.json確認を促す注意書き追加
- 推測でのコマンド実行を避ける警告文追加
- 実際の設定に従うことの重要性を強調

issue.title: Try to fix issue in nightly build

labels.name: release-note-none
labels.description: Denotes a PR that doesn't merit a release note.

labels.name: dco-signoff: yes
labels.description: Indicates the PR's author has DCO signed all their commits.

issue.body:
**What this PR does / why we need it**:
The nightly build fails from time to time on unit tests, when trying to create dashboard handlers based on a non-exists directory of dashboard yamls.

The directory name is computed with:
```go
dir := path.Join(os.TempDir(), fmt.Sprint(time.Now().UTC().Unix()))
```

This pattern is used in two additional unit tests. The guess is that the directory is aleady exist, when the tests assumes it isn't.

This commit gives a unique directory name for each one of the tests that uses the temp directory name pattern, to ensure each test is using its own directory. Also, try to make these test more robust, by taking logic out of the `By` functions, and by adding some error checks.

**Release note**:
```release-note
None
```

pull_request.body: Add `llms.txt` to Jenkins to disallow LLMs as we do it with robots.txt Some Background can be found at [llmstxt.org](https://llmstxt.org/) ### Testing done tried curl: ### Proposed changelog entries - also deliver a `llms.txt` file for LLMs ### Proposed changelog category /label rfe ### Proposed upgrade guidelines N/A ### Submitter checklist - [ ] The Jira issue, if it exists, is well-described. - [ ] The changelog entries and upgrade guidelines are appropriate for the audience affected by the change (users or developers, depending on the change) and are in the imperative mood (see [examples](https://github.com/jenkins-infra/jenkins.io/blob/master/content/_data/changelogs/weekly.yml)). Fill in the **Proposed upgrade guidelines** section only if there are breaking changes or changes that may require extra steps from users during upgrade. - [ ] There is automated testing or an explanation as to why this change has no tests. - [ ] New public classes, fields, and methods are annotated with `@Restricted` or have `@since TODO` Javadocs, as appropriate. - [ ] New deprecations are annotated with `@Deprecated(since = "TODO")` or `@Deprecated(forRemoval = true, since = "TODO")`, if applicable. - [ ] New or substantially changed JavaScript is not defined inline and does not call `eval` to ease future introduction of Content Security Policy (CSP) directives (see [documentation](https://www.jenkins.io/doc/developer/security/csp/)). - [ ] For dependency updates, there are links to external changelogs and, if possible, full differentials. - [ ] For new APIs and extension points, there is a link to at least one consumer. ### Desired reviewers @mention Before the changes are marked as `ready-for-merge`: ### Maintainer checklist - [ ] There are at least two (2) approvals for the pull request and no outstanding requests for change. - [ ] Conversations in the pull request are over, or it is explicit that a reviewer is not blocking the change. - [ ] Changelog entries in the pull request title and/or **Proposed changelog entries** are accurate, human-readable, and in the imperative mood. - [ ] Proper changelog labels are set so that the changelog can be generated automatically. - [ ] If the change needs additional upgrade steps from users, the `upgrade-guide-needed` label is set and there is a **Proposed upgrade guidelines** section in the pull request title (see [example](https://github.com/jenkinsci/jenkins/pull/4387)). - [ ] If it would make sense to backport the change to LTS, a Jira issue must exist, be a _Bug_ or _Improvement_, and be labeled as `lts-candidate` to be considered (see [query](https://issues.jenkins.io/issues/?filter=12146)).

issue.body:
📝 Description

The current Coding Editor page has several UI/UX shortcomings and responsiveness issues that affect usability across devices. The recent updates improved the dark theme, added icon-based buttons, and enhanced layout separation for editor and output. However, the following issues and improvements should be formally tracked:

**🔴 Problems Identified**

- Responsiveness Issues
- Editor and output containers previously overlapped or resized poorly on smaller screens.
- Buttons for Run Code, Reset, and Show/Hide Solution often wrapped inconsistently, breaking layout flow.

**UI/UX Inconsistencies**

- Lack of proper spacing between sections (description, editor, output).
- Difficulty badge colors were not optimized for dark mode, causing poor visibility.
- Action buttons lacked consistent styling, shadows, and spacing.

**Readability & Theme Support**

- Output block lacked distinction in light/dark themes.
- Editor height was fixed and not adaptive to screen size.
- Description text lacked padding and contrast for readability.

⚡ **Complexity::Level 3 — High**
